    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Let’s take a look at the troublemaker <em>f(x) = 1/x </em>which is discontinuous at 0 when defining it as a real function, that is as a function f: ℝ\{0} → ℝ. This too has a beautifully closed curve on the sphere.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
